Copying, Moving, renaming, Compress, archiving and deleting files.


Romvinf Files:

rm files                Remove file
rm -r dir               Removes directory and it's contents recursively
rm -f file              Force removal and never prompt for confirmation

Copying Files:

cp source_file destination_file             this copies source files to destination_file

cp src_file1 [src-fileN...] dest_dir        Copy source_files to destination_directory

cp -i                                       Run in interactive mode

cp -r                                       source_directory destination 
                                            copy src directory to the destination_file


Moving and rename files:

mv                                          Move or rename the Files
mv source destination                                                                              
mv -i source destination


Sorting Data

sort file                                    Sort the text in file


Sort options:

-k F                                        Sort by key. F is the feild number

-r                                          Sort in reverse source_directory

-u                                          Sort unique

Creating a collection of files:

tar [-] c|x|t f tarfile [pattern]           Create, extract or list contents of a tar file
                                            archive using pattern, if supplied


Tar Options:

c                                           Create a tar archive
x                                           Extracts files from the archive
t                                           Display the table of the contents(list)
v                                           Be verbose
z                                           Use compression
f file                                      Use this file


Compressing files to save space:

gzip                                       Compress Files
gunzip                                     uncompress Files
gzcat                                      Concatenates compressed Files
zcat                                       Concatenates Compressed Files

Disk Usage:

du                                        estimates files Usage
du -k                                     Display sizes in Kilobytes
du -h                                     Display sizes in human readable format
                                          


  
